\contentsline {subsubsection}{3.4 System Evaluation and Validation Criteria}{22}{section*.24}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{This section defines the evaluation and validation criteria derived directly from the identified business, user, and system requirements. These criteria establish a structured basis for assessing whether the proposed framework meets its intended objectives. In accordance with IEEE practices, the criteria are specified at a high level and are used later to guide system validation and performance evaluation, without presenting implementation results at this stage.}{22}{section*.25}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{The evaluation criteria are grouped into functional effectiveness, performance efficiency, risk and security impact, and usability and collaboration.}{22}{section*.26}%
\contentsline {paragraph}{3.4.1 Functional Validation Criteria}{22}{section*.27}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{These criteria evaluate the system'€™s ability to fulfill its intended functional requirements:}{22}{section*.28}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Threat-to-Test Mapping Accuracy: The system shall correctly map identified threat scenarios to relevant penetration testing techniques and attack vectors.}{22}{section*.29}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Threat Coverage: The system shall ensure that all high-risk threats identified during threat modeling are addressed through corresponding penetration tests.}{22}{section*.30}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Traceability: The system shall maintain clear traceability between assets, threats, vulnerabilities, test cases, and mitigation strategies.}{22}{section*.31}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Automation Effectiveness: The system shall reduce reliance on manual configuration during threat analysis and penetration testing activities.}{22}{section*.32}%
\contentsline {paragraph}{3.4.2 Performance and Efficiency Criteria}{22}{section*.33}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{These criteria assess the operational efficiency of the proposed framework:}{22}{section*.34}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Time Efficiency: The system shall reduce the time required to plan and execute security assessments compared to traditional isolated approaches.}{22}{section*.35}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Responsiveness: The system shall update threat models and risk scores promptly following penetration testing activities or threat intelligence updates.}{22}{section*.36}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Scalability Support: The system shall handle increasing numbers of assets, threats, and test cases without significant degradation in performance.}{22}{section*.37}%
\contentsline {paragraph}{3.4.3 Risk and Security Effectiveness Criteria}{22}{section*.38}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{These criteria measure the system'€™s effectiveness in supporting risk-driven security decision-making:}{23}{section*.39}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Risk Prioritization Accuracy: The system shall correctly prioritize threats and vulnerabilities based on impact, likelihood, and exploitability.}{23}{section*.40}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Adaptive Risk Management: The system shall demonstrate the ability to adapt to emerging threats through continuous feedback and threat intelligence integration.}{23}{section*.41}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Improved Risk Visibility: The system shall provide clear and actionable visual representations of risk levels to support informed security decisions.}{23}{section*.42}%
\contentsline {paragraph}{3.4.4 Usability and Collaboration Criteria}{23}{section*.43}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{These criteria evaluate how effectively the system supports user interaction and teamwork:}{23}{section*.44}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Ease of Use: The system shall provide intuitive interfaces that allow users to perform core security tasks with minimal training.}{23}{section*.45}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Collaboration Support: The system shall facilitate effective collaboration through shared documentation, notifications, and role-based access control mechanisms.}{23}{section*.46}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Report Clarity: The system shall generate clear, structured, and understandable reports suitable for both technical and non-technical stakeholders.}{23}{section*.47}%
